{
  "stem": "1282.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was organizer of the Revisionist movement.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'll never forget his words when he-- the powerful voice said, Jewish people look up in the sky, and the clouds are black.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They're getting blacker, and thicker, and they'll devour every Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Get out every way you can.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Don't stay here if you value your life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And if you value your kids, don't stay here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the words penetrated, and we heard them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it wasn't that easy because here we had, as I mentioned my mother had her adopted parents that were in their 80s-- the Hartsteins who adopted my mother.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my mother asked my father, how can we leave and leave these people alone?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They'll die.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, there was-- if something doesn't really hit you over the head, sometimes we think it may never happen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's hope.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had land that we still got some benefit from it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We still had a little more freedom than some of the Jewish Polish people that were already-- by 1941, '42 were already taken away from their home into camps.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It didn't happen in Czechoslovakia, I mean, in Carpathia, or in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were actually Hungarian at that time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Let's speak about Hungary because that time we were Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't happen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We still have freedom of movement, could ride the trains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We could move from one town to another town, but with restrictions.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, also my father says, what will I do?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What will-- where will I get started?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was somebody here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where do I get started?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yet he decided my uncle from this country sent to the family an affidavit to the Czech consulate in Prague.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father decided to go down and to try to get a visa for everybody, including my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
